        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Lai Siyao",
          "email": "laisiyao@whamcloud.com",
          "date": "2011-12-12 15:12:42.000000000",
          "tz": -480
        },
        "subject": "LU-649 io: DIO doesn't need lock i_mutex",
        "message": "LU-649 io: DIO doesn't need lock i_mutex\n\nThere is a dead lock if a file is written with with normal IO, and\nread with DIO at the mean time:\nregular write: extent lock -> i_mutex\nDIO read: i_mutex -> server take extent lock\n\ni_mutex taken at DIO read is redundant, because server will take\nextent lock to serialize with write and truncate. Removing it can\navoid the deadlock.\n\nChange-Id: I280559cebae5d04e4fd943bf3fbe82d67e07834b\nSigned-off-by: Lai Siyao <laisiyao@whamcloud.com>\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/b1_8"
    }
  },
